Managed to figure this out, just in case someone else needs this:
In order to get the list of defined streams, you will need a `KinesisExtendedBindingProperties` object to extract the bindings defined under `spring.cloud.stream.bindings` from your application.properties file. 
&lt;br&gt;
After that, just iterate over the Map returned by `kinesisExtendedBindingProperties.getBindings()` and use a `BindingServiceProperties` object to extract the binding attributes (`destination` in our case which represents the stream name).
```
        List&lt;String&gt; destinationStreams = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();

        kinesisExtendedBindingProperties.getBindings().forEach((k, v) -&gt; {
            Optional&lt;BindingProperties&gt; streamNameForBinding = Optional.ofNullable(bindingServiceProperties.getBindings().get(k));
            streamNameForBinding.ifPresent(bindingProperties -&gt; destinationStreams.add(bindingProperties.getDestination()));
        });
```

